courses.learning_outcomes:
On completion of this Master course, students should be able to:

1. understand the cellular and molecular basis of gastrointestinal cancers;
2. understand the principles of biomarker identification and application in gastrointestinal and liver diseases;
3. apply the principles of laboratory safety in research work;
4. appreciate the utility of animal models and the rapid development of molecular technologies for basic research in gastroenterology;
5. critically appraise basic science research work in gastroenterology;
6. apply basic laboratory techniques and perform data analysis in gastrointestinal research.
